### Node.js Agent Test Migration to node:test

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet illustrates the migration of various library tests within the node-newrelic project to use the built-in `node:test` module. This is a common testing framework update to improve test execution and consistency. It covers libraries like `ioredis`, `prisma`, `undici`, `memcached`, `nestjs`, `restify`, `nextjs`, `redis`, `hapi`, `kafkajs`, `langchain`, `openai`, `koa`, `mongodb`, and `pg`.

```javascript
// Example of migrating ioredis tests
// Original test setup might use Mocha/Chai

// New setup using node:test
const test = require('node:test');
const assert = require('assert');

test('ioredis versioned test', async (t) => {
  // Test logic for ioredis
  assert.strictEqual(1, 1);
});

// Similar migrations are applied to other libraries...
```

