### Web Framework Instrumentation with WebFrameworkShim (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This code illustrates the usage of the `WebFrameworkShim` class for writing instrumentation for web frameworks. This new API method, `newrelic.instrumentWebframework`, enables consistent feature parity, including Middleware metrics, across various frameworks like Connect, Director, Express, Hapi, and Restify.

```javascript
// Example using WebFrameworkShim (conceptual)
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// Assuming 'express' is a web framework
newrelic.instrumentWebframework(require('express'), 'express', (shim) => {
  // Instrumentation logic for Express using the provided shim
  // This shim provides methods for creating transactions, segments, etc.
});

```

